Add and Remove Remote Objects and Fields from Data Sync

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

To add an object:
Click the dropdown next to the connection. Select Edit Objects. Find the object to add by scrolling or using the search bar. Select the checkbox next to the object. Select the checkbox next to the fields that you want to sync.

To remove a field from data sync for an object already configured for sync:
From the Connections tab, select the connection associated with the object. Click the name of the object to see its columns. Fields already included for sync are selected. To add a field, select the checkbox next to the field. To remove a field, deselect the checkbox next to the field.

To remove an object from data sync:
From the Connections tab, select the connection associated with the object. Click the menu next to the object you want to remove. Click Disconnect Object. Click Disconnect.

Only field names with combinations of alphanumeric, dot, underscore, or dash characters are supported. If a connector includes field names that contain other special characters, like brackets, the sync fails.
